#: ../../C/chrome.rst:5
msgid "chrome"
msgstr "chrome"

#: ../../C/chrome.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../C/chrome.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from automotive slang via wargaming] Showy features added to attract users "
"but contributing little or nothing to the power of a system. \"The 3D icons "
"in Motif are just chrome, but they certainly are pretty chrome!\" "
"Distinguished from :ref:`bells-and-whistles` by the fact that the latter are"
" usually added to gratify developers' own desires for featurefulness. Often "
"used as a term of contempt."
msgstr ""
"[自動車スラングからウォーゲームを経て] "
"ユーザーを引きつけるために追加されるが、システムの力にはほとんどあるいはまったく寄与しない派手な機能。「Motifの3Dアイコンはただのchromeだが、確かにきれいなchromeだ!」"
" \\ :ref:`bells-and-whistles`\\ "
"とは、後者が通常、開発者自身の機能充実への欲求を満たすために追加されるという点で区別されます。しばしば軽蔑の語として使われます。"
